link_extraction_procedure.code:
# Extract all anchor links from raw DITA HTML
$anchors = [regex]::Matches($html, '<a[^>]+href="([^"]+)"[^>]*>([^<]*)</a>')
$anchors | ForEach-Object {
    $href = $_.Groups[1].Value
    $text = $_.Groups[2].Value.Trim() -replace '\s+', ' '
    if ($text -ne '' -and $href -ne '#' -and $href -notmatch '^http') {
        Write-Host "[$text] -> $href"
    }
}

method.code:
# Given a list of candidate slugs, find which ones are valid
$baseApi = "https://www.ibm.com/docs/api/v1/content/en/app-connect/13.0.x?topic="
$candidates = @(
    "dit-configuring-integration-server-record-messages",
    "dit-configuring-an-integration-server-to-record-messages",
    "commands-ibmint-generate-tests-command"
)

foreach ($slug in $candidates) {
    $html = (Invoke-WebRequest -Uri "$baseApi$slug" -UseBasicParsing -TimeoutSec 10).Content
    if ($html -notmatch '"primaryCategory":\s*"error"' -and $html.Length -gt 2000) {
        $title = if ($html -match '<h1[^>]*>([^<]+)</h1>') { $matches[1].Trim() } else { '?' }
        Write-Host "VALID: $slug  →  $title"
    } else {
        Write-Host "404:   $slug"
    }
}

step.action:
Replace the browser URL domain+path with the content API endpoint:
  Browser: https://www.ibm.com/docs/en/{product}/{version}?topic={slug}
  API:     https://www.ibm.com/docs/api/v1/content/en/{product}/{version}?topic={slug}
Use Invoke-WebRequest with -UseBasicParsing.
Verify the response is NOT a 404 (check for "primaryCategory": "error").
